		<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Both Air Manager &amp; Air Player have support for multiple Raspberry Pi Pico devices.<br />
You are able to use Air Manager or Air Player to drive LED's, Buttons, Switches, Rotary encoders etc. through the Pico.
</p><p>Within Air Manager you will find the installer that will flash your Pico, to make it possible to communicate with Air Manager or Air Player automatically using an USB connection.
</p>
<div style="background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.1); border: solid thin grey; padding: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center;&#125;&#125;"><a href="/index.php?title=File:Warning.png" class="image" title="Info"><img alt="Info" src="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/18px-Warning.png" decoding="async" width="18" height="18" srcset="/images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/27px-Warning.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cb/Warning.png/36px-Warning.png 2x" /></a> <span style="margin-top:-0px; padding-left:16px; display:block;">The Raspberry Pi Pico is supported from Air Manager 4.0 and up.</span></div>
<p><br />
</p>
<h1><span class="mw-headline" id="Prepare_your_Raspberry_Pi_Pico">Prepare your Raspberry Pi Pico</span></h1>
<p>1. Start Air Manager, and go to the Home tab.<br />
2. Click the Flash button on the top ribbon bar.<br />
3. Select the Raspberry Pi Pico.<br />
4. Unplug the USB cable from your Pico.<br />
5. Press and hold the BOOTSEL button and plug in the USB cable.<br />
6. It should show up as RPI-RP2 or similar, select this drive.<br />
7. Select the channel. Each Pico should have a unique channel assigned to it.<br />
8. Click Flash and wait until the installer is done.<br />
9. The Pico will show up among your devices and is ready to be used.
</p><p>Use the hardware API to interact with your Pico. Go to our <a href="/index.php?title=Air_Manager_Instrument_Logic_API#Hardware" class="mw-redirect" title="Air Manager Instrument Logic API"> Hardware API page</a> to learn more.
</p>
<h1><span class="mw-headline" id="Message_Port_Library">Message Port Library</span></h1>
<p>See the <a href="/index.php?title=Arduino#Arduino_Library_(SiMessagePort)" title="Arduino">Arduino Message Port Library</a> description for guidance.
</p>
